  "text": "In all cases, the rescaled correlations nicely approach a scaling function with increasing L, as predicted by the scaling law in Eq. [CITATION_1] . The finite-size approach to the asymptotic behavior is compatible with a L −1 behavior, as highlighted in the inset of the lower panel of Fig. 6 at fixed τ . We also observe that, for small values of τ , the scaling curves develop complex nonanalytic spikes in τ , whose magnitude and frequency increase with L, similarly to other dynamic situations as after sudden quenches [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] ; for larger τ dissipation tends to smear those apparent singularities.",
